<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880420-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Sealed Power Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> SPW </CO><IN> TNM </IN><TEXT>   Sealed Power Corp. said it agreed to purchase the automotive valve tappet business of Stanadyne Inc. of Windsor, Conn.    The Muskegon, Mich.-based parts manufacturing concern didn't disclose terms of the cash transaction, which is subject to regulatory review and approval by the boards of both companies.    Sealed Power's purchase would include Stanadyne's Tallahassee, Fla., manufacturing plant plus the machinery from its Garrett, Ind., and Windsor, Conn., facilities.    Stanadyne recently was merged into FLSI Acquisition Corp., a subsidiary of Forstmann Little andamp; Co. It had tappet sales of $44 million last year.    Sealed Power shares closed at $34.75, up $1, in composite trading yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange. </TEXT></DOC>